reviews.title: Review of SOULTASIA  Essex
reviews.body:
Love Soultasia.. only drawback at the Maldon party was when sister sledge were on ..one of the girls microphones didn't work so we couldnt hear her ..there is also a long wait between each performance.. ..the music in between is actually the best and really gets the crowd going 
Weather was perfect that evening too ..17th June 2022!

reviews.title: Review of SOULTASIA  Essex
reviews.body: We are regular festival goers and although the  bands were great the day was marred by poor organisation.  Unnecessarily Rude door and bar staff.  Too few staff resulted in very long queues. They wouldn’t allow people to take in water even though the temperature was over 30 degrees. Very expensive and poor quality food.  We will stick to the bigger and better run festivals in future which is a shame as this is close to home

reviews.body: Excellent time had x my daughters first music festival xxx

reviews.title: Review of SOULTASIA  Essex
reviews.body: Great event, well organised. Great atmosphere and brilliant free bus shuttle service. Been 2 years running and already got my ticket for next year

reviews.title: Review of SOULTASIA  Essex
reviews.body: Could have done without the hour of queuing got there in good time ,missed the first act entirely due to bag searches

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

 

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

reviewsDisplayFour.title: Review of SOULTASIA  Essex
reviewsDisplayFour.body:
I absolutely loved this event, a real step back in time! 

The only small criticism was that we queued for quite a while and nearly got into the event to be told that we were in the VIP queue and we had to go and join the standing only queue which was twice as long. A lot of people were not happy as you can imagine and were wanting to make a complaint, as at no point whilst queueing were there signs to tell us what queue we were in.  

Apart from that small blip, the event was brilliant!!!

reviewsDisplayFour.body: always good in maldon park seen tony Hadley last year looking forward to the next one .

reviewsDisplayFour.title: Review of SOULTASIA  Essex
reviewsDisplayFour.body: Soultasia was in a beautiful setting and proved to be a family-friendly day out. The warmth of everyone in attendance bowled me over. It felt safe, well organised and super friendly. Recommended to all who love music and just want to dance, reminisce and be merry with like-minded souls. I came with three friends, and we all agree we will be booking to go again next year!
